{"TopicId":149188,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Constant AOA SAS mode","CreatedByName":"Jonfliesgoats","CreatedById":168077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T06:14:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jonfliesgoats","CreatedById":168077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T06:14:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince there is no wind or turbulence to speak of in game, could we get a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E mode that holds a constant \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAOA\u003C/abbr\u003E? \u00A0I imagine this would be easy since alpha will always be the difference between the longitudinal axis of the craft. \u00A0You could set a\u00A0craft delivering a heavy payload to hold an efficient \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAOA\u003C/abbr\u003E without constantly compensating for the curvature of Kerbin. \u00A0This would also be handy for space plane reentry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T14:01:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might want to read this one:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149058-hold-this-angle-at-all-costs-sas-mode/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s exactly what you\u0027re suggesting and it\u0027s only 2 days old.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-03T14:02:11Z\u0022 title=\u002210/03/2016 02:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 3, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Tex_NL\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"luizopiloto","CreatedById":97503,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T14:34:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can place a small probecore at the desired angle, control from there and lock prograde... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}